Generating SessionDoc
SessionDoc provides you with a record of all of the rule objects that you created during the
session and is a powerful debugging aid when you use it with your tests.
It can be useful to use the JUnit tearDown hook point to force all the test methods in your test
class to output their SessionDoc:
@Override
          protected void tearDown() throws Exception {
          /*
          * Write out SessionDoc, to a directory named after the test
          * method.
          */
          final File sessionDocOutputDirectory =
          new File("./gen/sessiondoc/" + this.getName());
          sessionDoc.write(sessionDocOutputDirectory);
          super.tearDown();
          }
